From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] networking: add JournalMojoHandler for fennec://journal WebUI

Registers the fennec://journal WebUI page and implements a Mojo handler
that bridges the React frontend (src/ui/journal/) to the C++ RequestJournal.

The handler exposes:
  getEntries(n)       → JSON array of the n most recent JournalEntry objects
  exportJson(days)    → triggers a file download of the last N days
  clear()             → wipes the SQLite database
  subscribe(cb)       → registers a JS callback; fires on every new entry
  unsubscribe(id)     → removes the subscription

The handler implements RequestJournalObserver so it receives OnNewEntry()
callbacks on the IO thread and posts them to the renderer via a
mojo::AssociatedRemote.

PILLAR: Transparency
JOURNAL: Infrastructure — does not itself emit journal entries.

